Race.SpecificTitle: Parishwide Proposition -- 1 Mill Renewal - PC - 10 Yrs.
Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of St. Landry, State of Louisiana (the "Parish"), be authorized to continue to levy a special tax of one (1) mill on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $646,400 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2021 and ending with the year 2030, for the purpose of operating and maintaining a jail facility in the Parish?

Race.SpecificTitle: Faquetaique Gravity Drainage District No. 1 -- 5.72 Mills Continuation - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Faquetaique Gravity Drainage District No. 1 Proposition
(Millage Continuation)
Race.FullText: Shall Faquetaique Gravity Drainage District No. 1 of the Parish of St. Landry, State of Louisiana (the "District") levy a tax of five and seventy-two hundredths (5.72) mills on all the property subject to taxation in the District (an estimated $120,166 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2020 and ending with the year 2029, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, maintaining and/or operating gravity drainage works within and for the District, said millage to represent a twenty-eight hundredths of a mill (.28) increase over the 5.44 mills tax authorized to be levied through the year 2019 pursuant to an election held on October 17, 2009?
